From ff615d21c15c0f79587efab8519d08cbfb21227a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vinicius Teles <vinicius@improveit.com.br>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 12:43:46 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Bound every LLM and embedding call with an explicit timeout
 (CR036)

AI-01: send_to_model and generate_embedding constructed OpenAI clients with
no timeout, inheriting the SDK's 600s default. A hung provider connection
could stall a session-end hook, a switch_conversation, or the interactive
reception path for up to ten minutes with no error.

Bound the calls at client construction with per-role, env-overridable
timeouts (extraction 60s, reception 10s, embedding 15s) and a retry ceiling
(2). send_to_model takes timeout/max_retries params defaulting to the
extraction tier; reception passes the shorter interactive timeout; the
embedding client carries its own; runtime status reports the effective
values. No prompt, parse, or cost behavior changes (cost logging is CR044,
fallback model CR043).

RS006 CR036. Tests: send_to_model default+override, embedding client
timeout/retries, reception pass-through, status render line. 1917 passed,
ruff clean.
